<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-413] two flaws need addressing in the c tests that can cause false positive failures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-413</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1) createClient in testclient.cc (check all tests) is not correctly waiting for syncconnected to the server&lt;br/&gt;
2) there are some instances of while(xxx); in the test code, this could cause problems, really we need to&lt;br/&gt;
have some limit on the number of iterations (other than just the test, which may never return false), also the&lt;br/&gt;
loop should have some sort of sleep(100msec) (whatever time) in order to limit cpu use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
